      <td> 
        <div align="left"> 
          <p><font face="Verdana" size="-1"><b>Chapter 2: 
            The Road Less Travelled</b><br></font>
            <font face="Verdana" size="-2">(by <a href="http://www.eqraid.org/stories/members.cgi?action=showprofile&login=Cynister">Cynister Grimshadow</a> <a href="mailto:mileyt@home.com?subject=Interactive Fiction"><img src="graphics/email.gif" border="0" alt="send e-mail"></a> 
, added on March 5, 2001  06:33 PM CT (US))</font></p>
        </div>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <br>
  <table width="90%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
    <tr> 
      <td> <font face="Verdana" size="-1">Neriak, mountain fortress of the Dark Elves.  A cloaked figure makes his way towards the training halls of The Dead in Neriak's Third Gate.  Few where about at this hour and his passage was noted only by the ever watchful guards that roamed the city.  Trailing his hand over the ancient stone of the corridors the young man quietly mused to himself.  "How much these walls have seen, what stories could they tell"  Stopping for a moment the young man closed his eyes and let his mind travel where it would.  He could feel the storms that raged thru the darkness this night, slashing and howling thru the peaks of the Lavastorm Mountains.  The very air seemed charged with some eldritch energy that thrummed and vibrated throughout the stronghold of the Tier'Dal.  Resuming his slow pace he made his way towards his destination.  Few people in the land of Norrath would have seen or heard his passing. The Dark Elves, or Tier'Dal in the Elvish tongue, where by nature silent and possesed an inate ability to blend into the shadows.<br><br>Moments later he stood before a seemingly featureless wall marked only with a few faintly glowing symbols visable only to Tier'Dal eyes.  Passing his hand over the symbols and muttering a few syllables of the Dark Speech causes the faint outline of a doorway to appear. The rock shifts silently aside as he enters a narrow tunnel with a winding stair leading up into the darkness.  The stairs lead to a place of meditation known only to the Initiates of The Dead. The dark Necromancers, grave spell weavers of awesome power and the Shadow Knights, the military arm of The Dead.  The young man who now ascended the stairs to the Balek'Ci'Kel, the Tower of Sight, was a member of the latter.  His name was Cynister Grimshadow, Shadow Knight of the 5th Circle.  He thought he would spend a quiet night in meditation.  What he saw when he stepped onto the landing at the top of the stairway stopped him in his tracks.<br><br>Her back was to him as he passed thru the doorway and into the chamber of the Tower of Sight.  The place was so named for it was carved into the highest of peaks in the mountain range that housed Neriak.  A single large room with windows that looked down upon the vastness of Nektulos Forest.  Oft times several members of The Dead might be here meditating or merely watching the mist move thru the forest.  Tonight only she was there.  She turned and he gazed into those eyes, often heard in song or story, but never seen till this day. Those ancient eyes, so much older than the beautiful, ageless form they resided in, held him as surely as the strongest chains, he could not move, he could not speak.  A whisper of gossimer cloth as she crossed the room to him.  She looked up at him and a small smile played across her lips.  "Come Cynister, we have much to talk of this night.  There are portents in the air, The Father has spoken to me of you. Come.."</font></td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <br>
