      <td> 
        <div align="left"> 
          <p><font face="Verdana" size="-1"><b>Chapter 3: 
            In service of the Queen</b><br></font>
            <font face="Verdana" size="-2">(by <a href="http://www.eqraid.org/stories/members.cgi?action=showprofile&login=Cynister">Cynister Grimshadow</a> <a href="mailto:mileyt@home.com?subject=Interactive Fiction"><img src="graphics/email.gif" border="0" alt="send e-mail"></a> 
, added on March 8, 2001  12:51 PM CT (US))</font></p>
        </div>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <br>
  <table width="90%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
    <tr> 
      <td> <font face="Verdana" size="-1">The Queen of Neriak! At that moment he must of looked rather foolish gaping at her, quite unable to say anything.  Apparently it showed on his face too, for it brought a brief chuckle from her.  That quickly faded as her face turned stern again, "Come! Sit with me and hear what it is I command of you."  Settling fluidly into one of the many divans in the chamber she beckoned to him.  Quickly he approached and kneeled before the one who commanded the unswerving loyalty of The Dead. <br><br>"What is commanded of me, my queen.  I live to serve."  "There is something that has been lost to us for many years young Cynister.  An item of power and symbol of the house Thex.  Long it was lost but our agents have finally found the location of this talisman.  I did make sacrifice to The Father and seek guidance for I was not sure who to send on this errand. A rogue of great skill perhaps, or a Grave Lord from the ranks of the Shadow Knights, mayhap a dread Warlock sumommed from his arcane studies to do my bidding."  A smile again flitted across her lips.  "What did my visions show me instead? A whelp, a knight of the 5th circle, not even skilled enough to call forth the weakest of spells.  The Father showed me you, Cynister.  You are to be my champion for this task."  Leaning back she stared intently at him.  Her eyes narrowed and a feeling of heat washed over him as he mustered his will and returned her gaze.  "Fail me and none shall ever know you walked this earth.  Succeed and your place among the Grave Lords is assured my young servant."  "I shall not fail you my queen. What task must I accomplish for you?"<br><br>He held himself well Christianos Thex mused to herself as she observed the young man who knelt so still before her.  What was it about him that intrigued her? Surely not his physical appearance, he was not overly handsome and he was much heavier muscled than most Tier'Dal, giving him a somewhat brutish demeanor.  But the calm that radiated from him was something else entirely.  Ahhh that was it. Focus.  Even at such a young age he was more focused than many of his elders.<br><br>"You must retrieve the pieces of the Thex Mallet and return them here to me.  The Thex Mallet has been found and must be reforged.  You know of this talisman?"  "Aye my queen, the symbol of the House Thex, long lost in the Combine Wars."  "Your instuctors have taught you well Cynister, yes that is the item of which I speak.  Now take yourself to see Loveal in the Lodge of The Dead. He will provide you with information and equipment for the task ahead of you."  Rising, he bowed low before her.  "As you command, my queen."  As he turned to leave she called to him softly, "Cynister.  It will be long before you see me or the walls of this city again. Your quest will take you far from home and test your will.  Prepare yourself well.  Do not fail me."  He silently nodded to her and turned his steps towards the Lodge of The Dead.</font></td>
    </tr>
