      <td> 
        <div align="left"> 
          <p><font face="Verdana" size="-1"><b>Chapter 4: 
            Leaving Home</b><br></font>
            <font face="Verdana" size="-2">(by <a href="http://www.eqraid.org/stories/members.cgi?action=showprofile&login=Cynister">Cynister Grimshadow</a> <a href="mailto:mileyt@home.com?subject=Interactive Fiction"><img src="graphics/email.gif" border="0" alt="send e-mail"></a> 
, added on March 20, 2001  12:15 AM CT (US))</font></p>
        </div>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <br>
  <table width="90%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
    <tr> 
      <td> <font face="Verdana" size="-1">Loviel S'Nez stared at the whelp in front of him, a sneer playing across his lips as he looked at the young night holding his new armor and weapons.  Leaning closer to the young man he suddenly hammered his mailed fist into the young knights midsection.  Cynister grunted in pain but his facial expression did not change, nor did he take his eyes off of the Shadow Knight master.  His baleful eyes just inches from the young man's face Loviel spat out syllables in the Dark Speech.  "If you should think that the Queen's desires for your success shall afford you any protection from me should you fail her... You would be most sadly mistaken young apprentice.  Fail Her and you shall die a thousand deaths, each more excruciating than the last!"<br><br>Bowing low before S'Nez Cynister turned and made his way from the armory with his bundle of armor and weaponry.  It was time to prepare.  Once back at his quarters he quickly began to lay out his new gear and prepare for the journey that lay ahead.  The first task in his quest for the Thex Mallet had been explained to him by Loviel when he first arrived at the armory. <br><br>"The Queen would have you outfitted with arms and armor forged by the finest of Tier'Dal smiths.  She wishes to afford you some small chance to succeed in your mission apparently."  The Shadown Knight master sneered at his apprentice as he tossed him the bundle.  "You were a fine pupil Cynister, but I fear I shall never see you again." Shrugging, he turned away and fetched a folded letter from a table nearby.  Quickly S'Nez read thru the letter and tossed it into the nearby firepot.  "The first step of your mission is to travel to the Lavastorm Mountains.  There is a Paladin of some renown, one Sir Lindeal, who has taken it upon himself to interrupt the trade routes with our ancient stronghold of Najena.  Find him, challenge him and kill him.  Should you live thru your encounter with him, bring me proof of his death, his testimony should do well." Chuckling to himself he eyed his student.  "A testimony eh? What fools that cannot remember their purpose lest they read it from a parchment!  Let the fires of hatred rage from within when you find this Paladin and leave his torn body for the carrion feeders."<br><br>Cynister mused over this as he outfitted himself, carefully placing and securing each piece of banded chain armor in the proper order.  That finished he strapped on the belt that held his new sword and dagger.  Pulling the blade free from it's sheath he stared at the fine workmanship of the blade. A Combine blade, made by the ancient craftsmen of the Northlands, still keen and rust free after so many hundreds of years.  The light flickered and shimmered across the surface of the finely wrought steel.  The blade itself seemed to give of a faint glow.  Smiling to himself he sheathed the blade and secured his pack containing rations, bandages and the like to his back.  He looked around his sparse chambers one last time and quietly made his way out of the city and set his feet upon the road to Najena, nestled deep in the Lavastorm Mountains.</font></td>
    </tr>
