      <td> 
        <div align="left"> 
          <p><font face="Verdana" size="-1"><b>Chapter 5: 
            The gates of Najena</b><br></font>
            <font face="Verdana" size="-2">(by <a href="http://www.eqraid.org/stories/members.cgi?action=showprofile&login=Cynister">Cynister Grimshadow</a> <a href="mailto:mileyt@home.com?subject=Interactive Fiction"><img src="graphics/email.gif" border="0" alt="send e-mail"></a> 
, added on April 2, 2001  12:51 PM CT (US))</font></p>
        </div>
      </td>
    </tr>
  </table>
  <br>
  <table width="90%" border="0" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1">
    <tr> 
      <td> <font face="Verdana" size="-1">Cynister sat at the mouth of the cave that had become his home these past weeks and meditated, his eyes staring out into the darkness, his ears absorbing the sounds of the night.  The moon was almost full again, almost 4 weeks gone by since he left the stronghold of Neriak to begin his mission.  In that time he had grown much.  When he finally found this accursed Paladin he felt he would be equal to the task.  The Lavastorm Mountains were teeming with hostile creatures, more than enough to constantly improve his skills.  When the Shadow Knight masters evaluated him upon his return he was sure to be advanced to the 9th rank or perhaps higher.  Finally he would be instructed in the use of necromantic spells.  The young man wrenched himself back to the painful reality that none of that would come to pass if he did not find his prey and quickly.  The Paladin was wise and clever, several times Cynister had come upon his handywork but to late to find him at the scene.  Dead goblins, vanished supplies, guards slain in the very shadow of ancient Najena.  Channeling his frustration into a seething hatred for this servant of Marr Cynister focused his mind as the night passed to dawn.<br><br>The fire goblins had informed him that a supply of minerals was being taken to Neriak this day.  Cynister felt sure he would finally flush out his quarry today.  Silent and hidden above the trail close by the broken gates of Najena he watched and waited. The goblins milled around the huge ogre porters as their packs were loaded and secured.  Closing his eyes, Cynister strained his exceptional hearing for the faintest signs that the Paladin was near.  After several minutes he heard what he had hoped for all these weeks.  Someone was moving down the slope towards the pass the caravan must move thru to begin the trek to Neriak.  Opening his keen eyes, the young shadow knight scanned the rocks above him.  There! Flitting from behind a large boulder was a large figure, a human!  Clad all in dull chain armor, smeared over with lava ash the Paladin blended in almost completely with the terrain.  Almost.  Cynister quickly and silently made his way up the slope and behind his target.  The Paladin had chosen a small flat area on the slope to set up his ambush, screened from the road by rocks this natural platform was ideal for launching a barrage of magic and missiles and allowed an easy escape.  There would be no escape today for him though.  Mentally preparing himself Cynister silently stepped onto the rock shelf where his opponent crouched, his attention taken by the activity below.<br><br>Cynister drew his blade from the scabbard slowly, making sure there was an audible hiss as the blade came free.  The man in front of him tensed for a moment expecting the blow.  When none came the human slowly stood to his full height and turned.  The Teir'Dal and Human faced each other for several seconds.  At last the Human spoke. "So at last they have sent you.  I hope you are prepared to meet your dark god today evil one."  He pulled his blade free from his back scabbard, a large two-handed sword.  Nothing else needed to be said, both knew that no surrender would be given and no quarter asked.  Silently they came together the sounds of their battle masked to those on the ground below by the noises of the caravan.  The Paladin, slow and powerful and the Dark Elf, swift and agile, traded a flurry of blows but the heavier blade of the Human beat aside Cynister's lighter blade and scored a crushing blow across his shoulder. His mail rent and blood flowing down his arm Cynister staggered back and went down to one knee.  Eyes gleaming the Paladin raised his blade for the finishing blow.  Grinding his teeth together Cynister channeled the pain into hate, the hate into strength.  Spinning aside as the Human's sword bit into the rock where he had been a moment ago he snapped to his feet, spun past his over-extended foe and brutally slashed him across the back of neck. Staggering upright the Paladin clutched at his neck and as he did so Cynister came in low and slashed again upwards across the knights midsection.  The combine blade cleaved thru the chain links and into the flesh beneath.  Slumping back against the rocks the knight attempted to call upon his god of light for healing but Cynister quickly stepped forward and unleashed the power of hatred, channeled thru his outstretched hand directly into the Paladin's chest.  The smoking corpse crumpled to the ground. Sagging to his knees Cynister could barely maintain conciousness long enough to bind his wounds.  <br><br>Opening his eyes Cynister realized he must have passed out after binding his injured shoulder.  Dizzy, he crawled over to the body beside him and searched thru the pouches till he found what he needed. The Testimony of Sir Lindeal.  Gingerly he made his way down to his camp to take rest and mend his wounds before making his way back to Neriak.</font></td>
    </tr>
